The paper deals with capacity and coding algorithms for a multiuser communication system with feedback, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of virtual queues and rate regions suggests a focus on queueing theory and stochastic processes (cs.SI), while the outer bound analysis and modifications to the algorithm suggest a focus on optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of feedback and capacity analysis suggests a focus on information theory and machine learning (cs.LG).
